description:
It's finally time for the big one: The Shiminami Kaido. Beginning with a short ferry ride across the water, we then ride across six islands, and cross six bridges. Making sure to take our time and not to rush, we spend our day making our way across the inland sea of Japan with the final goal of reaching Shikoku - Japan's fourth largest island.

Each bridge is a large spike in elevation, meaning our legs will be sore from an entire day of sharp ups and downs. On the final island, we have the option to detour to Kirosan Park lookout for spectacular views of the sunset overlooking the 2nd Kurushima-Kaikyo Bridge.
